caption: Was great showed me a great time and had a blast

Stumbled upon this gem and couldn’t be more pleased with the food and the service. Everything is prepared fresh and the sushi rolls were 👌🏻. Sam, the owner, was gracious and an amazing host. Will definitely be back!
Awesome food and even better service. The owner, Sam, is very gracious and polite. Highly recommended!!

Very delicious and fresh sushi. I ordered the Sashimi bento and one of the specialty maki. The sashimi came with fresh cut wasabi in addition to the regular wasabi all restaurants have, which was a nice touch. The staff and owner were nice and the food was well made.  I have worked in sushi restaurants before and I can tell you that the cuts I received were thick and the portion sizes were very reasonable for the price. Depending on how hungry you are, entrees are about $20+, while sushi would be about $25+ a person.  The atmosphere is casual and pretty. If you want fresh and good quality fish, give it a shot.

Great food and atmosphere! The guacamole fusion role was a perfect blend of asian and hispanic. The crazy roll and shrimp tempura rolls were also delicious. Hard to choose which rolls to order as so many sounded good! We even got to try the sake mimosa which is a brand new drink and will be a refeshing brunch option. Next time we are trying the ramen! If you love sushi and are in the city, this should definitely be on your list!
Such a hidden gem, honestly. Great, fresh ingredients. The owner is so hospitable and the staff is top notch. We love coming to this location!
Really good ramen and creative and fresh sushi.
Fresh and tasty. Im not a big sushi roll person I prefer sashimi and this place always has tasty fresh fish
Incredibly huge selection of fish and tasty fresh sushi in the food stalls

Excellent food and the guys working the counter, I'm assuming they own this place, offer the best customer service and are very friendly. I went there for the first time recently and this is my "go to" spot for Tsukiji Fish Market going forward.

This place is an absolute gem! I took my food to go and it was perfectly packed including the Karage chicken which tasted great! The food and customer service of this place is outstanding . Highly recommend anyone who is looking at trying out a new sushi 🍣 place! They offer curbside pick up and delivery too!
So fresh, so delicious! This place is a great value and great sushi. Some of the best I've had. Very generous! Who needs AYCE when you can have what you need and it's better.

We order from here about once a week. Not only is the sushi always fresh and excellent, the customer service is superb. We requested a bit more wasabi and asked to pick it up. Not only did the restaurant deliver it, they also sent sashimi. Support this restaurant. They are the best.
The owners are so welcoming and the sushi was great! Highly recommend

This place has been on my list forever and I just never made it. Ordered their lunch special & tamago for delivery and I’m impressed. Nigiri lunch special came with soup and salad and the fish was really good. I requested no octopus, squid or scallop in the nigiri if possible so not sure if this is the standard lineup but I was happy. The California roll was also nice and I liked that there was tobiko on the outside. Not for sure on all the pieces but I think it included salmon, tuna, yellowtail, and two others, one that tasted like mackerel. Nevertheless I was happy and will order again.
Wonderful sushi - excellent service! Will visit again
Great neighborhood sushi spot, extremely fresh.

Delicious Sushi Rolls! Me and my partner went during happy hour (4pm-7pm) and enjoyed the amazing Chicago Fire, Dragon, Crunchy Shrimp, and Ocean Jalapeños! The owner was our waiter and he was very welcoming and made me an amazing mango margarita!
Unagidon is not cheap but worths the price, good portions of fresh fish. Not too crowded.
Great food and amazin service highly recommend the roll with mango on it n the green tea cheesecake for desert 🔥🔥🔥

Our favorite Japanese place in Chicago. The menu is outstanding and varied, much more than just a traditional sushi restaurant as my boyfriend doesn't love sushi. The ramen and homemade curry are wonderful and remind us so much of the food we actually ate in Tokyo last year. The staff is gracious and kind, and the location/new outdoor tables are wonderful for a night out. Try this place out, you will not be disappointed.
Great food and friendly owner. Also a huge menu with  some unusual options. Will def be going back.

Best non-omakase sushi I’ve had in the past 2 years in Chicago! This stuff is fantastic. From specialty rolls to maki to sashimi, everything here is great. Delicious miso soup and seaweed salad as well. Packaged perfectly for take out, ready to go right on time.

One of the tastiest sushi rolls I've ever had. If you can take a bit of heat, do not miss their Spicy Fusion Roll, it's a Japanese-Mexican fusion that will titillate your palate. Everything else is full of flavors too. We got the Tako Yaki, Sashimi Bento Box, and Ikebukuro . The interiors are warm and service even warmer. Sam takes great care of the guests and was super kind to offer us dessert on the house. Can't wait to come back 🍣🍙
Stopped in for a late lunch and had a few rolls and grilled mushroom skewers. All was great. Service was excellent and friendly. Will be back for sure.
Extremely fresh. Everything on the menu is great and won't set you back $200. Check out brunch for a sake mimosa.
Great food great service!  Sam and Gabriela made us feel right at home.  The sushi was very fresh and delicious.  We will definitely be back again soon.
Placed an order online through the website. I was certain that I ordered it for delivery since I had to put my address in. Waited for 1 hour, called restaurant and turned out it was for pickup.

First of all, WOW!  I did not have a chance to visit this spot before it came under new ownership, but let me just say that Sam is the best! It must be incredibly hard to stay positive as a restaurant owner right now, but Tsujiki Fish Market has nothing to be afraid of. In just 2 hours, their flavorful food and friendly atmosphere became my new favorite sushi hub in the neighborhood.  My friend and I basically ordered the whole menu: Edamame, Seaweed Salad, Octopus, Tako Yaki, Gyoza, and 4 oustanding rolls; the Fat Buddah, the Volcano, the Creamy Spicy Tako, and the Ocean Jalapeno. Every new bite we took was better than the last. You can absolutley tell these rolls are made with skilled hands and the culinary team knows whats up!  Thanks for the kind hospitality and good eats! I'll be back :)
If you like sashimi, you should absolutely try the Sashimi combo (Matsu Sashimi). All the fish is so fresh. The yellowtail and salmon are outstanding!!! Ramen is great as well.

Fantastic communication on dietary concerns. Excellent customer service. I was even called about a nigiri replacement when my Saba (my favorite sushi fish.) was unavailable.  The quality of the sushi fish and appetizers was great. The inari with tomago, ikura and mushroom was great.  Everything was beyond what I expected (but hoped for.) in a pick up sushi to go situation. I appreciated their staff going above and beyond for me- having celiacs disease and a lot of questions.  I was not glutened either, So that was great too.

Tying sushi for the first time sushi chef recommended to try peachy and ommera and I have to say I enjoyed it very much.Amazing curry beef don as well. Knowledgeable sushi chefs helped made my experience here very very good. There créeme brûlée is amazing.
Really really the best sushi I have had in Chicago. Super fresh and creative. It’s a must! The ocean roll and the Chicago fire were our favs!
Tried this place for the first time recently and was blown away with quality of sushi and service. New owner Sam was awesome.  Definitely adding to the rotation.

I just moved to Chicago from LA, and have tried a few sushi restaurants here. HOLY COW this is hands down the best, and honestly better than every LA spot as well. Every single cut of fish melts in your mouth, and the service is incredible. Under new ownership and Sam is amazing. Thank you so much for an incredible first dinner here. Can't wait to come back already!!
(Translated by Google) The food is very tasty  (Original) La comida muy rica
Tsukiji is my favorite sushi restaurant in all of Chicagoland. I highly recommend just about everything on the menu. The wait staff is first class and they know how to treat their customers right

I celebrated my PhD yesterday in this great restaurant. happy to tell that we had a fine evening and the restaurant was clearly one of the reasons for the fruitful gathering. The stuff  participated in a sweet style, the cuisine was extremely good and my friends were very  pleased. We shall absolutely visit again for more celebrations. thanks very much.
Repeat customer.  Food and customer service is always top notch.
We had great dinner in Tsukiji. Food is amazing, fresh and very tasty. The best maki rolls. They melted in my mouth. Service is very professional and nice.  Highly recommended.

I've ordered from here a good number of times. Today I ordered with my office and enjoyed a truly wonderful tempura bento box. It was filled with beautiful and fresh veggies and seafood. Can't get enough of this place, can't wait to visit in person!
Just go
Good all around fish place tho I think if you know what you want specifically...you could do better.  Aka ramen or sushi.  But if you have differing needs then a good spot.

I adore this place! They prepare sensational dishes, their menu is rich, The cook in that place is very trained, I like very much eating all their food. The dishes are always fresh and tasty, the attitude towards the customers  is agreeable. I often eat in this place and I was never disappointed. I recommend this place.
Absolutely love this place. Great flavors to match its beautiful presentation.
The meals and service were ahead of my expectations. We really liked the vibes of this spot. Nice place to take my family out for lunch.
Super Fresh Fish.  Great Service.
Great food, wonderful service! Worth a visit

I found it ha excellent food and a great atmosphere. Better than Umai so far as ramen goes, and better than Yuzu so far as sushi & sashimi goes. Service was highly attentive and very friendly, too.  And you usually can walk in any night and be seated. (They deserve more business. Under-hyped. And with decent if not good curb appeal, I don't get it. Anyhow.)  About as pricey as Furious Spoon, although incomparably superior in about every other respect.

I've only actually dined in once. I usually get delivery/pickup. The food here is always good. The one time I dined in, I tried food other than just sushi. My friend and I shared the tako yaki and kimo (chicken liver) skewer. I usually order the okonomiyaki when I get carry out- it's a good sized order...I can get 2 or 3 servings from it. I've tried the salmon volcano aburi nigiri, Alaska roll, crazy roll, and island roll all of which are so good. I almost always order the salmon volcano aburi and the crazy roll. One time I ordered a bento box for pickup and wasn't able to pick up the food I ordered until 2 or 3 hours later than what I had scheduled.  The restaurant called me to check if I was still going to pick up my food which was sweet, considering I had already paid for the food. When I got there to pick up the food, the employee who handed me the food told me they had remade the food for me so it would be fresh. How amazing is that??  Street parking isn't too tough to find. Most of it is not free. I'm not sure how busy the restaurant usually gets. It usually seems empty when I'm there to pickup food so I'm guessing most of the business is delivery/carryout orders.
Friendly staff, delicious food, and diverse menu.
Traditional food...
Best sushi in Chicago.
I lived in Japan and the fish is NOT flown in from Tsukiji at all. It's obviously frozen and not good at all. What a major disappointment.
Your place shouldn't say fish market if it's not a fish market!
Fantastic
Great food selection, great execution, our waitress was amazing, food was great! Definitely more than I expected and very good call to pop in there while walking down the street

It was an absolutely amazing lunch on our first visit. The restaurant was cozy with sense of Japanese authenticity. We ordered couple of appetizers, I have been on a hunt for an okonomiyake a Japanese seafood vegetable pancake with a savory Japanese mayo and this place delivered! It was delicious that it reminded me of how my aunt with make it, the takoyaki another appetizer it’s like a squid ball fluffy and delicate was tasty and just pure yum in my belly! We also had sushi/sashimi bento and a pork tonkatsu bento both has side salad very refreshing and generous side with cup of rice and miso sou! This place has a sense of authentic Japanese food with wide variety and selection! We will be back to try more of what the restaurant had to offer. Oh btw it’s street parking. And a little pricey but it is worth it!

Got there on a snowy night, not very busy, got seated. Ordered promptly, was extremely hungry.  Proceed to wait 40 minutes for my two simple rolls to be delivered.  Then waited another 20 minutes for a simple beef curry rice fish, which never came.  Despite repeated questions about where the food was, they kept saying it was coming (It was not) and offered no explanation as to what was taking so long.  Eventually I told them I was leaving, and when pressed they admitted they were putting delivery orders that came in after my order on priority.  Worst dining experiance in 3 years living in Chicago. The food was okay, but after the service I'd prefer gas station sushi any day.

Loved it! Most fish was great, a few were not as fresh as they could have been. Great service, great choices. As authentic as possible for the Midwest.

caption: Good environment for individuals or groups. The nigiri was really good.
Extensive menu of delicious food. Worth checking out.

Nothing will blow you away  But their consistency over multiple visits and the quality across half the menu that we've had keeps us coming back.  The yellowtail and green onion benchmark is solid.  Do try the tornado roll.
Food was excellent and service quick. Will go there again
Wow place. The most delicious and fresh sushi, maki and other food. I think this is the best place ever. We will be back very soon The service is outstanding as well.

Best sushi in west loop/west town.  When was the last time you had real fresh minced wasabi and not the green colored horseradish served as wasabi?  Great food!!!!   Good prices.  Legit sushi with variety of hot and cold dishes.  Staff is super friendly and attentive.   I can’t say enough.  This is by far mine and all of friends favorite spot Friday night after a long week.  Tall Asahi please!!
They have great service their food is so good and they are the best,I really recommend this place I really like it everyone is so nice.
This place is great the service is good and the sushi is good too I recommend this place
This is a clean market of sea food at Japan, you can found so many sea food product here, such as fish, crab, and many other sea food. Also you may try food street here.

I usually go to the same sushi spots, but I thought I give it a try. It's decent but it's not my favorite. Reasonable price, but the service was so slow. The ramen was pretty good. They do have some interesting rolls like grilled chicken sushi rolls with unagi sauce. If you click like on the Facebook page, they will give you a complimentary edamame. I do recommend the rice bowls!!
Food is good, but I got the food position after eating here .
Decent food, slightly pricey
Good food but pricey.

It was a quiet night when we were there. The cooked food was quite good but the fish on the sushi roll was kind of warm, and the taste was so so. The menu is long and has different kinds of food for everyone. The service is good.

This place was my ‘want to go’ places for sushi. The outside looked authentic and nice. We came around 6 and we were only ones there. There were 2-3 more tables when we were leaving.  The atmosphere is quiet. I prefer quiet places but this place was too quiet where I had to talk so soft.  Chicken karagae was okay but pretty salty. Only ate few pieces. I ordered sushi set. Omg. Too much rice. You know how sushi buffets have lot of rice to fill you up? Well, this place had more rice than those places. And the fish was so dry. One of the fish melted in my mouth... not in a good way. My friend had ramen and it was okay. We had so much leftovers.  Overall, the sushi was worst I ever had and over priced.
Food was great and fresh, but very expensive.
The seared tuna was great, but the maki was a chewy. Also could use some ambiance. It was very quiet.
Very fresh, tasty fish. Great atmosphere

Open Monday to Friday only at Merch Mart 10am to 4pm.
Ramen was delicious, staff was very cool and this place has a great vibe!
Good service. Good food.
Oh heck yeah!  Great music, awesome atmosphere, friendly service and delicious food!
I came here with friends out of curiosity after reading about it in a good guide. I had my doubts, since I suspect it was a promotion. But thoroughly satisfied.

We ordered foods from this restaurant for our staff lunch and there was a miscommunication in our order. Anyway, the restaurant took initiative to fix the problem and made another dish for our one of staff. We truly appreciated and the gentle man took time to explain the issue to easy on us. We truly thought that that was a great and professional manner and customer service. WE def go back to this restaurant. Thank you for the good quality food and service.
Not good as people says.

This place serves some very authentic Japanese food. I really love the Hokkaido style entree, and beef yakitori. Very good sushi, and they have real fresh wasabi. Staff is friendly too and they provide good service. This is a good restaurant for dining alone, great for a group too.

Tsukiji Fish market has great sushi and sashimi. The ramen is good too if on the expensive side and not as good as high five or furious. The karaage chicken appetizer is delicious. Such good fried chicken. Get their tea too it's pretty authentic.
Best Ramen in Chicago hands down.. the food is amazing here.
Like the fresh sashimi here
Some of the best sushi in Chicago. Well priced for the great quality
Delicious and byob

Best Ramen I ever had!  I am having a hard time finding anything that compares to how delicious it is.  Service was great!  We went around 1pm and service was very fast and personable.  Highly recommend.
Food was fantastic, as was the service. They have okonomiyaki and it is amazing! Strongly recommend that and the takoyaki, both were excellent. Great atmosphere!
Amazing Sushi, the Katsudon was also delicious
Very fresh and they have some unique presentations
Did not try the sushi, but the tonkatsu was decent.
Butterfly across the street is for ignoramuses. Go here instead.
Miso soup!

The sushi here is fantastic! The okonomiyaki is one of the best things I've ever tasted. Along with the sushi they have other options (sashimi, udon, ramen, bento boxes). Everything I have tried has been amazing. The staff is extremely friendly. The chefs are great.

Awesome!  I love the vibe in here.  We sat with a view of the street - got a lot of what they had.  Poke was good, rainbow roll was good also.  I would prob put this right up there with Elephant from maybe a dozen or so sushi places in Chicago that I can think of.
Something was not right with the spicy tuna roll last night, but I ate it anyways. Terrible food poisoning today! I can't recommend.

Yummy, yummy in my tummy.  I order from here all the time. after I saw Butterfly's quality slipping, I thought I'd try the new kids in town... That was over a year ago, and many orders later, I can say it's everything you'd hope for in a sushi restaurant. The staff here are among the friendliest at any sushi place I've ever been to. The rolls are delightful, fresh, consistent and just delicious. They have some out of the norm ones too, which I love! delivery, carry out or dine in, take your pick, they're all great!
Super fast delivery. Good quality sushi and a very large menu. I have only ordered delivery from here, but the space looks modern and inviting.

I am sad to say it took me this long to order from this restaurant.  I did take out tonight and ordered the Udon beef and the teriyaki Don chicken and it was fantastic!  Shame on me for taking this long to go here.  I certainly hope they do well.  this is a "go to" spot for me now.
This restaurant has the most authentic Hawaiian Poke I've ever had outside of Hawaii. The sushi is fantastic, seriously this place is a must try. Trust me, you'll be hooked, nothing else compares!!

I was told by the concierge to check out Butterfly. As I walked past, I noticed that it was packed and decided to look elsewhere. To my surprise, right up the road is a unassuming restaurant that claims to be a fish market. When I walked in I briefly glanced over the menu & asked" How often do you get a fish delivery?" The woman replied "Everyday." What restaurant wouldn't say that? The ambiance was warm, carefully decorated and very intimate. So, I gave it a try. Boy, did I make the right decision. I have been eating sushi for 27 years and sampled the best from all over the globe. If a sushi bar has poor Uni, then most likely, all the fish will be poor. Am, our waitress, was attentive and I never had an empty water glass. You are going to need it when you taste Chef's handmade wasabi. This is priceless. The fish was outstanding..fresh, crisp and sweet. The Uni melted in my mouth and the Sashimi was tender & flavorful.  From the Uni, to the fresh cracked crab legs. The portions were filling and the presentation was too beautiful to eat. Can somebody please call Anthony Bourdain? If you want to eat at Chicago's best kept secret, make this a travel destination. I have to go to confession as the food was that sinful!

Multiple trips have been very satisfying. Sushi is very good, portions and price are solid. Favorite item is the Ikebukuro, but there is a lot of ground to cover for those wanting to sample the whole menu. The decor is much more pleasing than Butterfly was when it filled the same space. Consider going here next time you want sushi at Grand and May.

I love this place and I wish more people would go here!!  The sushi is outstanding!!  Seems like too many people are going to Butterfly when they should really be going here!!  And, it's BYOB or should I say, "BYOS" for bring your own sake!
Place and service was nice. Sushi was tasty but I got terrible food poisoning yesterday from it. :(

Saw this opened after the other sushi placed moved & thought I would give it a try.  A lot of interesting rolls & food on the menu.  Ones we had were great, will be back to try others & all the noodles selections.  This is my new sushi place.
